SIMPLE: gratuitous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gratuitous
<hw>Gra*tu"i*tous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>gratuitus</ets>, from <ets>gratus</ets> pleasing. See
<er>Grate</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, <er>Gratis.</er>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Given without an equivalent or recompense; conferred without
valuable consideration; granted without pay, or without claim or merit;
not required by justice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We mistake the <qex>gratuitous</qex> blessings of Heaven for the
fruits of our own industry.</q> <rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not called for by the circumstances; without reason,
cause, or proof; adopted or asserted without any good ground; <as>as, a
<ex>gratuitous</ex> assumption</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Acts of <qex>gratuitous</qex> self-humiliation.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincye.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Gra*tu"i*tous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Gra*tu"i*tous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gratuity</ent>⟦br⟧
